An Act relative to student representative relative to student representative voting rights.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 38M of Chapter 71 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official
2 Edition, is hereby amended by striking in lines 9 through 14 the phrase “Said chairperson shall
3 be an ex-officio, nonvoting member of the school committee, without the right to attend
4 executive sessions unless such right is expressly granted by the individual school committee.
5 Said chairperson shall be subject to all school committee rules and regulations and shall serve
6 without compensation.” and inserting in place thereof the following:-
7 “School committees of cities, towns, and regional school districts shall recognize two (2)
8 student representatives, to be elected by the student bodies of all secondary schools within the
9 district, prior to the first day of June in each year. Said representatives shall be allowed to vote
10 on all matters before the committee. Student representatives shall be subject to all school
